definition:
Someone descended from Shuham who was a man of the tribe of Dan living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.23; 
 son of: Dan (H1835H); also called Shuham at Num.26.42,43; 
Group of chu.shim (חֻשִׁים "Hushim" H2366B) 
 § Shuhamites, of Shuam "pit-digger"
 descendants of Shuham, the son of Dan
